03:41.471 --> 03:43.306
There's food all around us.

03:43.348 --> 03:46.143
Look-- those are edible

03:43.348 --> 03:46.143
fungi called truffles.

03:46.185 --> 03:48.103
Those are deer turds.

03:49.104 --> 03:50.731
Okay, well, we're all

03:50.772 --> 03:53.274
going to learn

03:50.772 --> 03:53.274
a lot this weekend.

03:53.316 --> 03:56.277
That pasta

03:53.316 --> 03:56.277
was fabulous, Reese.

03:56.319 --> 03:57.738
How's Larry?

03:57.779 --> 03:59.156
He won't stop

03:57.779 --> 03:59.156
fighting with Mom.

03:59.198 --> 04:00.490
The other day she

03:59.198 --> 04:00.490
barged in on him

04:00.532 --> 04:01.909
when he was

04:00.532 --> 04:01.909
in the bathtub.

04:01.950 --> 04:03.451
So he stood up,

04:01.950 --> 04:03.451
yanked off her wig,

04:03.493 --> 04:04.452
and dried

04:03.493 --> 04:04.452
himself with it.

04:04.494 --> 04:05.871
Very thoroughly.

04:05.913 --> 04:06.955
(laughing)

04:06.997 --> 04:08.916
That Larry's a keeper.

04:08.957 --> 04:11.752
Yeah, it's so great he's

04:08.957 --> 04:11.752
not a backstabbing weasel.

04:12.753 --> 04:15.296
A weasel is

04:12.753 --> 04:15.296
a horrible animal.

04:15.338 --> 04:19.009
Susan, I've been thinking

04:15.338 --> 04:19.009
about the gift you gave Jamie.

04:19.051 --> 04:21.220
I know, Lois, and you don't

04:19.051 --> 04:21.220
have to worry about it.

04:21.261 --> 04:23.555
I brought gifts

04:21.261 --> 04:23.555
for the other boys, too.

04:23.597 --> 04:24.723
Yes!

04:24.765 --> 04:26.183
Sitting here

04:24.765 --> 04:26.183
looking interested

04:26.225 --> 04:27.101
finally pays off.

04:27.142 --> 04:28.309
No, Susan,

04:27.142 --> 04:28.309
that's not

04:28.351 --> 04:29.310
what I meant.

04:29.352 --> 04:30.979
I'm uncomfortable

04:29.352 --> 04:30.979
with the amount.

04:31.021 --> 04:32.355
It's awfully extravagant.

04:32.397 --> 04:33.899
Oh, you think

04:32.397 --> 04:33.899
everything's extravagant.

04:33.941 --> 04:37.318
Now, I know how much

04:33.941 --> 04:37.318
little Dewey likes candy,

04:37.360 --> 04:39.196
so I got him

04:37.360 --> 04:39.196
a professional

04:39.238 --> 04:42.241
cotton candy machine.

04:44.743 --> 04:46.411
(gasps)

04:46.453 --> 04:47.913
Susan, what are you doing?

04:47.955 --> 04:49.330
We don't own a circus.

04:49.372 --> 04:50.874
Well, now you can

04:49.372 --> 04:50.874
feel like you do.

04:51.833 --> 04:53.001
Now, I'm sorry,

04:51.833 --> 04:53.001
but you two boys

04:53.043 --> 04:53.794
are going to have

04:53.835 --> 04:55.336
to share a gift.

04:55.378 --> 04:57.338
I'm giving you the Mustang.

04:57.380 --> 04:58.757
Oh, my God!

04:57.380 --> 04:58.757
You're kidding!

04:58.799 --> 04:59.633
REESE:

04:58.799 --> 04:59.633
Thank you!

04:59.674 --> 05:00.717
I never believed

05:00.759 --> 05:02.343
anything Mom

05:00.759 --> 05:02.343
said about you.

05:02.385 --> 05:03.720
Susan, you can't

05:02.385 --> 05:03.720
give them a car.

05:03.762 --> 05:04.972
Mom, technically

05:03.762 --> 05:04.972
this is a transaction

05:05.013 --> 05:06.514
between Aunt Susan and us.

05:06.556 --> 05:08.349
And I'm willing to hire

05:06.556 --> 05:08.349
a lawyer to enforce it.

05:08.391 --> 05:10.227
You want to go there,

05:08.391 --> 05:10.227
I'll go there.

05:11.061 --> 05:12.062
You know, Lois,

05:12.104 --> 05:14.355
usually when someone

05:12.104 --> 05:14.355
gives gifts,

05:14.397 --> 05:15.523
people say thank you.

05:15.565 --> 05:18.860
Well, I'm sorry, this...

05:15.565 --> 05:18.860
sudden generosity,

05:18.902 --> 05:21.613
coming from you,

05:18.902 --> 05:21.613
is a little baffling.

05:21.655 --> 05:23.364
Oh, I'm sorry that the concept

05:23.406 --> 05:25.159
of opening your heart and giving

05:25.200 --> 05:26.952
is so baffling to you.

05:26.994 --> 05:28.369
LOIS:

05:26.994 --> 05:28.369
I don't know,

05:26.994 --> 05:28.369
some people might not

05:28.411 --> 05:29.955
think of it as giving.

05:29.997 --> 05:32.291
Some people might think of it

05:29.997 --> 05:32.291
as just showing off.

05:32.332 --> 05:34.417
Oh, here we go! We're only

05:32.332 --> 05:34.417
three hours in, and we've

05:34.459 --> 05:36.253
already received

05:34.459 --> 05:36.253
our first visit

05:36.295 --> 05:38.213
from the Queen Bee

05:36.295 --> 05:38.213
of Moral Superiority.

05:38.255 --> 05:41.300
Oh, and here's the victim,

05:38.255 --> 05:41.300
right on schedule!

05:41.340 --> 05:43.302
I became the victim

05:41.340 --> 05:43.302
on my prom night

05:43.342 --> 05:45.386
when I walked into

05:43.342 --> 05:45.386
the garage and caught

05:45.428 --> 05:47.555
my boyfriend having sex

05:45.428 --> 05:47.555
with my sister

05:47.597 --> 05:49.266
on the hood of my car!

05:53.020 --> 05:54.855
(whispering):

05:53.020 --> 05:54.855
Where do I look?

05:54.896 --> 05:57.524
There's

05:54.896 --> 05:57.524
nowhere  to  look.

06:01.069 --> 06:03.238
Dad, please, you don't

06:01.069 --> 06:03.238
have to do this.

06:03.280 --> 06:04.405
We love this car.

06:04.447 --> 06:05.699
We promise we

06:04.447 --> 06:05.699
won't try to drive it

06:05.740 --> 06:07.117
until you say we can.

06:07.159 --> 06:09.328
You think your mom and I

06:07.159 --> 06:09.328
were born yesterday?

06:09.368 --> 06:11.496
How can you do this?!

06:13.081 --> 06:14.415
Boys, please.

06:14.457 --> 06:16.084
I know this is hard

06:14.457 --> 06:16.084
for you to understand,

06:16.126 --> 06:17.127
but you're just going

06:17.169 --> 06:18.503
to have

06:17.169 --> 06:18.503
to realize that

06:18.545 --> 06:20.214
your mom and Susan are crazy.

06:20.255 --> 06:22.257
The sooner you learn

06:20.255 --> 06:22.257
to accept that, the better.

06:26.303 --> 06:27.428
Okay, girls,

06:27.470 --> 06:29.139
we got a nice cozy cave

06:27.470 --> 06:29.139
to sleep in,

06:29.181 --> 06:30.307
a big roaring fire...

06:30.349 --> 06:31.933
I'd say things are looking up.

06:31.975 --> 06:33.227
That isn't enough firewood.

06:33.268 --> 06:34.435
You have to keep

06:33.268 --> 06:34.435
the fire going

06:34.477 --> 06:37.105
all night

06:34.477 --> 06:37.105
to keep animals away.

06:37.147 --> 06:41.442
Okay, Meagan, Kirsten,

06:37.147 --> 06:41.442
go get more firewood,

06:41.484 --> 06:45.113
and make sure it's not this dumb

06:41.484 --> 06:45.113
green stuff Francis got.

06:45.155 --> 06:47.532
Whoa, whoa, you girls

06:45.155 --> 06:47.532
aren't going anywhere.

06:47.574 --> 06:49.117
It's dark out there.

06:49.159 --> 06:50.952
I'm in charge here

06:49.159 --> 06:50.952
and I'm telling you to stay.

06:52.329 --> 06:54.248
I vote Brittany

06:52.329 --> 06:54.248
to be our new leader.

06:54.289 --> 06:55.165
All in favor?

06:55.207 --> 06:56.457
ALL:

06:55.207 --> 06:56.457
Aye!

06:56.499 --> 06:57.458
I accept.

06:57.500 --> 06:58.668
Now you guys

06:57.500 --> 06:58.668
get the firewood

06:58.710 --> 07:00.461
and you guys move the blankets

07:00.503 --> 07:02.047
to the dry part

07:00.503 --> 07:02.047
of the cave.

