14:16.356 --> 14:17.398
Meagan.

14:17.440 --> 14:18.899
Meagan!

14:18.941 --> 14:19.900
Huh?

14:19.942 --> 14:21.486
Shh!

14:21.528 --> 14:23.404
I have something

14:21.528 --> 14:23.404
very important to tell you.

14:23.446 --> 14:24.989
What?

14:25.031 --> 14:26.907
Brittany told me

14:25.031 --> 14:26.907
that Donny Frost

14:26.949 --> 14:29.118
said that he likes you,

14:26.949 --> 14:29.118
but she won't tell you

14:29.160 --> 14:31.078
'cause she thinks

14:29.160 --> 14:31.078
you're stuck up.

14:31.120 --> 14:32.913
No way!

14:32.955 --> 14:35.792
And also, she said those shoes

14:32.955 --> 14:35.792
she said were cute on you

14:35.834 --> 14:37.126
aren't cute on you at all.

14:37.168 --> 14:39.086
They're actually dorky.

14:39.128 --> 14:41.506
Why would she say

14:39.128 --> 14:41.506
such mean things?

14:41.548 --> 14:43.216
I think it's because

14:41.548 --> 14:43.216
she's a two-face.

14:43.257 --> 14:44.718
But that's not important.

14:44.759 --> 14:46.720
What is important

14:44.759 --> 14:46.720
is that a girl like that

14:46.761 --> 14:48.137
should not be the leader.

14:48.179 --> 14:49.764
You should be the leader.

14:49.806 --> 14:52.350
You're more honest

14:49.806 --> 14:52.350
than she is and prettier.

14:52.392 --> 14:54.769
Me? The leader?

14:54.811 --> 14:57.188
Totally. Together,

14:54.811 --> 14:57.188
we could make this

14:57.230 --> 14:59.232
the best Buttercup troop ever.

14:59.273 --> 15:02.861
All I need you to do

14:59.273 --> 15:02.861
is untie my hands.

15:02.902 --> 15:04.070
Okay.

15:06.030 --> 15:08.949
You are not going

15:06.030 --> 15:08.949
to regret this.

15:08.991 --> 15:10.785
(groans)

15:10.827 --> 15:11.786
(body thuds)

15:11.828 --> 15:13.663
Buttercups are always loyal!

15:13.705 --> 15:16.875
Think about that

15:13.705 --> 15:16.875
while you're sleeping outside!

15:18.501 --> 15:19.794
Yeah, driving's cool.

15:19.836 --> 15:21.546
I do all my thinking

15:19.836 --> 15:21.546
when I drive.

15:21.588 --> 15:24.883
Of course, sometimes I drive

15:21.588 --> 15:24.883
and I don't think, I just drive.

15:24.924 --> 15:28.428
But no matter where I drive

15:24.924 --> 15:28.428
or how much I drive,

15:28.469 --> 15:30.971
I find that people

15:28.469 --> 15:30.971
are still people.

15:31.013 --> 15:33.182
That is so true.

15:33.224 --> 15:34.975
Thanks for letting me

15:33.224 --> 15:34.975
wear your jacket.

15:35.017 --> 15:36.853
Sure. Let me ask

15:35.017 --> 15:36.853
you something.

15:36.895 --> 15:39.439
Do you remember last week

15:36.895 --> 15:39.439
when I said "hello" to you,

15:39.480 --> 15:42.066
and you said, "Look what's

15:39.480 --> 15:42.066
trying to talk to me?"

15:42.108 --> 15:43.777
Did I?

15:43.818 --> 15:45.612
So, are you nicer to me

15:43.818 --> 15:45.612
now because you realize

15:45.653 --> 15:47.447
we have more in common

15:45.653 --> 15:47.447
than you thought,

15:47.488 --> 15:49.657
or because you find our

15:47.488 --> 15:49.657
differences intriguing,

15:49.699 --> 15:52.076
or because now

15:49.699 --> 15:52.076
I have a car?

15:52.118 --> 15:54.245
Uh, probably the car.

15:52.118 --> 15:54.245
Cool.

15:54.287 --> 15:56.997
Sometimes I love high school.

15:57.039 --> 15:58.999
Hey, why don't we drive

15:57.039 --> 15:58.999
somewhere

15:59.041 --> 16:01.628
so we can have

15:59.041 --> 16:01.628
a little privacy?

16:02.879 --> 16:05.005
